data.content:
Your code **doesn't use `Thread.Abort`** at all. It only uses `Thread.Start()`, `Thread.Join()`, and `Thread.Sleep()` — all of which work identically in .NET 8. No migration is needed for this snippet.

That said, the code would benefit from modernization using `Task`/`Parallel`:

```csharp
public class SimpleWorker
{
    public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items)
    {
        Parallel.ForEach(items, item => Process(item));
    }

    private void Process(WorkItem item)
    {
        Thread.Sleep(100);
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    }
}
```

